1.0
---

- Threading support: Fractal calculation should now scale up pretty much
  linearly with the number of CPU cores in the system.

- Add 22 palettes that are compiled into the program executable and thus
  always available, thereby removing the dependency on external palette
  files.

- Save important parameters to ~/.gfractrc

- Crop tool.

- Huge internal code re-organizations.

- Lots and lots of other changes.


0.33
----

- Removed a compiler warning

Jasper Lievisse Adriaanse <jasper@nedbsd.nl>:

 - Makefile tweaking for OpenBSD


0.32
----

- Pressing Enter while zooming activates the selected zoom region.

- Add "Reset fractal" menu commmand.


0.31
----

James W. Morris <james@jwm-art.net>:

 - Add -DGTK_DISABLE_DEPRECATED, fix all resulting errors.

 - Add 'Apply' button to attributes dialog.


0.3
---

- Use GTK2.

- Allow palettes with unlimited number of entries.

- User specified coloring algorithms.

- Palette interpolation.

- Change over to using C++.

- Documentation changes


0.21
----

- Big endian support. (Tom Blench, tom@bris.ac.uk)

- Can display time used for calculating fractals.

- Code formatting cleanups.

- Changed from using tmpnam to mkstemp.

- Clarified the license issue by putting the program under GPL.


0.2
---

- 4:3 aspect ratio limitation removed.

- Minimum image size limit of 320x240 removed.

- Changed the handling of dead child processes to better coexist
  with (future) threading. This also removed the reliance on
  BSD signal semantics.

- Palette cycling.

- Added a pixmap file (gfract.xpm) that you can use, for example,
  as an appicon in Window Maker.

- Better documentation.

- Lots of bugfixes.

- First really public release.


0.1
---

- First (semi)public release.
